glish:  see  Timbrell  ."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":9,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705202,"age":18,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705205,"age":29,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705206,"age":31,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705207,"age":45,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705208,"age":47,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Timbrell was born in 1540, in Preston, Gloucestershire, England, his father, Steven Timbrell, was 21 and his mother, Lady Anne Ferneley, was 22. He had at least 1 daughter with Alice Mary Aitkins. He died in January 1617, in Oxfordshire, England, at the age of 77, and was buried in Preston on Stour, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1540–January 1617":"1540–jaanuar 1617","1540–1617":"1540–1617","1553–1634":"1553–1634","1572–1625":"1572–1625","1519–1604":"1519–1604","1518–1595":"1518–1595","January 1617":"jaanuar 1617","1572":"1572","1571":"1571","1572 ":"1572","17 Jun 1595":"17. juuni 1595","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1634":"1634","about 1539":"1. jaanuar 1539","1587":"1587","1553":"1553","1585":"1585","1540":"1540","1595":"1595","1519":"1519","1518":"1518","1617":"1617","1604":"1604","1549":"1549","1625":"1625","London, Middlesex, England":"London, Middlesex, England","Preston, Gloucestershire, England":"Preston, Gloucestershire, England","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England","Bengeworth, Worcestershire, England":"Bengeworth, Worcestershire, England","Preston-on-Stour, Gloucesters